answer:
The uppercase branch adds ord('a') as its base offset instead of ord('A'), remapping uppercase letters into the lowercase range.

```python
def caesar(text, shift):
    result = ""
    for ch in text:
        if ch.isupper():
            result += chr((ord(ch) - ord('A') + shift) % 26 + ord('A'))
        elif ch.islower():
            result += chr((ord(ch) - ord('a') + shift) % 26 + ord('a'))
